.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fI\fIM-C-e\fR\fR (\fIerlang-end-of-function\fR) - Move to the end of the current or following Erlang function. With an numeric argument (ex \fI\fIC-u 2 M-C-e\fR\fR) the function skips backwards over this many Erlang functions. Should the argument be negative the point is moved to the end of a function below the current function.

.RE

.sp
