.SS "Edit - Alignment"


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fI\fIC-c C-a\fR\fR (\fIalign-current\fR) - aligns comments, arrows, assignments, and type annotations around the cursor.

.RE

.IP
.nf
Example:

sum(L) -> sum(L, 0).
sum([H|T], Sum) -> sum(T, Sum + H);  % recurse
sum([], Sum) -> Sum.   % base case

-record { two :: int(), % hello
          three = hello :: string(),    % there
          four = 42 :: int() }.

becomes:

sum(L) -> sum(L, 0).
sum([H|T], Sum) -> sum(T, Sum + H); % recurse
sum([], Sum)    -> Sum.             % base case

-record { two           :: int(),    % hello
          three = hello :: string(), % there
          four  = 42    :: int() }.

.fi

.SS "Syntax highlighting"

.PP
The syntax highlighting can be activated from the Erlang menu. There are four different alternatives:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
Off: Normal black and white display.

.RE

.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
Level 1: Function headers, reserved words, comments, strings, quoted atoms, and character constants will be colored.

.RE

.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
Level 2: The above, attributes, Erlang bif:s, guards, and words in comments enclosed in single quotes will be colored.

.RE

.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
Level 3: The above, variables, records, and macros will be colored. (This level is also known as the Christmas tree level.)

.RE

